         <li class="touchcarousel-item"><img width="683" height="460" src="http://www.drew.edu/undergraduate/wp-content/uploads/sites/106/lee3-683x460.jpg" class="attachment-thepeople wp-post-image" alt="lee"> <h2 class="type">Passionate Faculty</h2> <h2 class="name">Seung-Kee Lee</h2> <h2>Associate professor</h2> <p>I teach history of philosophy, philosophy of religion, existentialism and my research focuses on Kant and German idealism. I received the 2012 President’s Award for Distinguished Teaching at Drew. I am also the coordinator of the Drew University Philosophical Society (DUPS).</p> <p><strong>Ph.D., Catholic University of America</strong></p> </li> 
         <li class="touchcarousel-item"><img width="683" height="460" src="http://www.drew.edu/undergraduate/wp-content/uploads/sites/106/anderson2.jpg" class="attachment-thepeople wp-post-image" alt="anderson"> <h2 class="type">Passionate Faculty</h2> <h2 class="name">Erik Anderson</h2> <h2>Professor</h2> <p>I once had a student tell me it took them 10 years in the workplace before they realized they’d been employing all along the analytical and logical skills learned studying philosophy at Drew. I’m now the NEH Distinguished Teaching Professor of the Humanities. I’m also a bebop fan with a cycling problem.</p> <p><strong>Ph.D., University of Colorado</strong></p> </li> 
        </div>
